# Frontend Structure Conventions

Follow `docs/Frontend-ن»£ç پç»“و‍„ن¼کهŒ–وŒ‡هچ—.md` (especially آ§7.4). Summary:

## Where code goes

| Code | Location | Condition |
|------|----------|-----------|
| Route page entry | `routes/{domain}/{page}.tsx` | One file per `APP_ROUTES` entry |
| Page logic | `routes/{domain}/hooks/use-{page}-page.ts` | State, effects, orchestration |
| Page-only UI | `routes/{domain}/components/` | Exactly 1 route page; no workflow reuse |
| Shared domain UI | `components/{domain}/` | 2+ route pages OR 1 page + `features/workflow` |
| Cross-domain layout/auth | `components/layout/`, `components/auth/` | No single-page blocks |
| Primitives | `components/ui/` | No business semantics â€” no domain words in filename |
| Generic enum/filter select | `components/ui/options-select.tsx` | Map from `lib/labels.ts`; no hardcoded options in pages |
| Workflow adapter | `features/workflow/workflows/` | Open via `useWorkflow().open()` |
| HTTP | `api/{domain}.ts` | One namespace per backend resource |
| DTO types | `api/types/{domain}.ts` | Same domain as API |
| Pure helpers | `lib/` | No React; unit-testable |
| Demo date anchor | `lib/demo-clock.ts` | `DEMO_TODAY`, `resolveLast7DaysRange()` â€” never hardcode demo dates |
| Audit query builders | `lib/audit-query.ts` | Shared filter â†’ API query mapping |
| Tests | `tests/` | Mirror `src/` subpaths; `@tests/` for fixtures/utils |

## Component placement decision

1. Business semantics? If no â†’ `components/ui/`
2. Cross-domain layout/auth? â†’ `components/layout/` or `auth/`
3. Count consumers: route pages + workflow imports
4. One route page only, no workflow â†’ `routes/{domain}/components/`
5. Two+ route pages, or workflow reuses UI â†’ `components/{domain}/`
6. Promote: second route page imports from `routes/*/components/` â†’ move to `components/{domain}/`
7. Demote: `components/{domain}/` only used by one page with no workflow â†’ `routes/{domain}/components/`

Workflow pattern: reusable form in `components/{domain}/` (e.g. `CredentialForm`); thin wrapper in `features/workflow/workflows/`.

## New component checklist

1. List all importers (route pages + workflow)
2. Pick directory per table above
3. Never put domain-named files in `components/ui/` (`budget-*`, `org-*`, etc.)
4. Update آ§7.4 inventory in the guide when adding shared components

## Page template

`{page}.tsx` â€” compose only; call `use{Name}Page()` from `hooks/use-*-page.ts`.

Page hooks:
- Use `useApis()` (optional `injectedApis` for tests)
- Use `useAsyncResource` for data; expose `error` + `refresh`
- Audit list pages: prefer `use-audit-list-page` (wraps `useFilteredResource`)
- Return a flat view model; no JSX

## Routes (single source of truth)

- Paths: `ROUTES` in `config/routes.ts` only â€” never hardcode `/org/...`, `/budget/...`, etc.
- Metadata: `ROUTE_META` holds `path`, `label`, `icon`, `requiredPermissions`, optional `badgeKey`
- New route checklist:
  1. Add `ROUTES.*` key and `ROUTE_META` entry
  2. Add `APP_ROUTES` lazy import
  3. Add path to `NAV_GROUP_LAYOUT` in `config/nav.ts`
  4. Create `routes/{domain}/{page}.tsx` + `hooks/use-*-page.ts`

## API dependency injection

- Consume APIs via `useApis()` in hooks, workflows, and shared components
- Do not `import { xxxApi }` in business code
- Tests: `createMockApis()` + `renderHookWithProviders(..., { apis })` from `@tests/utils`
